      },
      {
        "beatId": 11,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Direct the investigation toward a conclusion which later proves to be erroneous."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 5,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 1,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Erroneous conclusion",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 12,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. Reveal facts about suspects, through interrogations and the discovery of clues."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. Flight, or disappearance of one or more suspect."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "C. Develop a sense of urgency. Raise the stakes or make it evident that if the mystery is not solved soon, there will be terrible consequences."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 6,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 1,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Facts about suspects",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 13,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. The investigation should broaden to put suspicion on other characters."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. Information gathered through interviews or the discovery of physical evidence, should point toward the solution, although the relevance may not yet be apparent."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 7,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 1,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Broaden investigation",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 14,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. The sleuth’s background is revealed as the sub-plot is developed. Tell the reader what drives the protagonist, what haunts or is missing in his or her life."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. Make it clear that the sleuth has a personal stake in the outcome, either because of threat to his or her life, or the possibility of revelation of matters deeply disturbing to the protagonist on an emotional level."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 8,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 2,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Sleuth's background",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 15,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "Change of focus and scope of the investigation. This is the pivotal point in the story where it become evident that the sleuth was on the wrong track. Something unexpected occurs, such as the appearance of a second body, the death of a major suspect, or discovery of evidence which clears the most likely suspect. The story must take a new direction."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 9,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 1,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Change of focus",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 16,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. Reveal hidden motives. Formerly secret relationships come to light, such as business arrangements, romantic involvement's, scores to be settled or previously veiled kinships."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. Develop and expose meanings of matters hinted at in Act I., to slowly clarify the significance of earlier clues."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 10,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 1,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Reveal hidden motives",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 6,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. The sleuth reveals the results of the investigation. The reader, as well as the protagonist and other characters, are given an opportunity to review what is known and assess the possibilities."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. The solution of the crime appears to be impossible. Attempts to solve the crime have stymied the sleuth. Misinterpretation of clues or mistaken conclusions have lead him or her in the wrong direction, and logic must be applied to force a new way of grasping an understanding of the uncertainties."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "id": 11,
        "imageId": null,
        "lineId": 1,
        "places": [],
        "position": 0,
        "seriesLineId": null,
        "tags": [],
        "templates": [],
        "title": "Reveal results",
        "positionWithinLine": 0,
        "positionInChapter": null,
        "fromTemplateId": null
      },
      {
        "beatId": 5,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. Have the sleuth review the case to determine where he or she went wrong."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. Reveal the chain of events which provoked the crime."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "C. The crucial evidence is something overlooked in Act I, which appeared to have been of little consequence at the time it was first disclosed. That evidence takes on new meaning with information disclosed in Act III."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "D. The sleuth (and perhaps the reader, if a keen observer) becomes aware of the error which remains undisclosed to the other characters."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
