      {
        "beatId": 1,
        "bookId": null,
        "characters": [],
        "description": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "A. The Climax - a dramatic confrontation between the sleuth and the perpetrator in which the sleuth prevails. The more “impossible” the odds have been, the more rewarding the climax will be."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "B. Resolution - Revelation of clues and the deductive process which lead to the solution. Establish that the case has been solved and justice has been served to the satisfaction of all involved (except, the villain)."
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
